-- SOUTH AFRICA DAYBOOK: Manufacturing, State of Nation
-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 2011-02-10T06:25:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-10/south-africa-daybook-manufacturing-slows-zuma-presents-state-of-nation.html
South African manufacturing growth
slowed in December, according to the median estimate of 10
analysts surveyed by Bloomberg News.  Factory production, which accounts for about 15 percent of
the economy, increased 3.8 percent in December from 4.6 percent
in November, according to the estimates, which ranged from 0.7
percent to 6.5 percent. Statistics  South Africa  releases the
data at 1 p.m. in  Pretoria .  The statistics agency also releases mining production data
for December at 11:30 a.m. local time. Output climbed 9.6
percent in November from a year earlier with gold production
increasing 2.1 percent and manganese ore surging 47 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vernon Wessels in Johannesburg at 
